      <head>Adolf Weisse</head>

      <div>
        <p>Distinguished character actor, who studied in Vienna, worked in Kassel (1879), Berlin
          (1885-86), and Cologne (1887-), then at the Deutsches Theater (German People's Theater) in
          Vienna (1889-), becoming its Director in 1902. Adolf Weisse was the father of <ref
            cRef="entity-000951">Hans Weisse</ref>.</p>
      </div>
